  "description": "Permanent volume changes caused by the application of isotropic pressure are taken into account in this model by including, in addition to the shear and tensile failure envelopes in the strain-softening/hardening model, a volumetric yield surface (or “cap”). For simplicity, the cap surface, defined by the “cap pressure” \\(p_c >\\) 0, is independent of shear stress; it consists of a vertical line on a plot of shear stress versus mean stress. The hardening behavior of the cap pressure is activated by volumetric plastic strain, and follows a piecewise-linear law prescribed in a user-supplied table",
  "property_groups": [
    {
      "name": "Properties",
      "description": "Material properties for the 'double-yield' zone constitutive model. Assign the model with 'zone cmodel assign double-yield [range ...]', then set these with 'zone property <keyword> <value> [range cmodel-name double-yield]'.",
      "properties": [
        {
          "keyword": "bulk-maximum",
          "symbol": "K_{max}",
          "description": "maximum elastic bulk modulus, K_{max}",
          "type": "FLT"
        },
